@node CORAL "Coral Reef"

@{b}Coral Reef@{ub}

Color   = Blue
Rarity  = HL(C1)
Type    = Enchantment
Cost    = UU
Artist  = Amy Weber

Text(HL): When Coral Reef comes into play, put four polyp counters on it.
          <0>: Sacrifice an island to put two polyp counters on Coral Reef.
          <U>: Tap target blue creature you control and remove a polyp
          counter from Coral Reef to put a +0/+1 counter on any target
          creature.

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_C.guide/CREEF}

@endnode
@node DARKM "Dark Maze"

@{b}Dark Maze@{ub}

Color   = Blue
Rarity  = HL(C2/C2) / 5E(C)
Type    = Summon Wall (4/5)
Cost    = 4U
Artist  = Rob Alexander (HL) / Rob Alexander (HL) / David Seeley (5E)

@{b}NOTE@{ub}: There are THREE different artworks for this card.

Text(5E): <0>: Dark Maze can attack this turn as though it were not
          a Wall. At end of turn, remove Dark Maze from the game.

Text(HL): <0>: Dark Maze can attack this turn. At end of turn, remove
          Dark Maze from the game. Dark Maze cannot attack the turn it
          comes under your control.

Flavor Text: @{i}"Stray not into the path of darkness, or be lost forever."
              ---Baki, Wizard Attendant@{ui}

Flavor Text: @{i}"The path of faith is fortunately fraught with failure."
              ---Irini Sengir@{ui}

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_D.guide/DARKM}

@endnode
@node FORGE "Forget"

@{b}Forget@{ub}

Color   = Blue
Rarity  = HL(U1) / 5E(R)
Type    = Sorcery
Cost    = UU
Artist  = Mike Kimble

Text(5E): Target player chooses and discards two cards, then draws as
          many cards as he or she discarded in this way.

Text(HL): Target player chooses and discards 2 cards from his or her hand.
          If that player does not have enough cards in that hand, his or
          her entire hand is discarded. The player then draws as many
          cards as he or she discarded in this way.

 @{b}NO RULINGS@{ub}

@endnode
@node GIALB "Giant Albatross"

@{b}Giant Albatross@{ub}

Color   = Blue
Rarity  = HL(C2/C2)
Type    = Summon Albatross (1/1)
Cost    = 1U
Artist  = David A. Cherry / David A. Cherry

@{b}NOTE@{ub}: There are TWO different artworks for this card.

Text(HL): Flying
          <1U>: Bury all creatures that damaged Giant Albatross this turn.
          The controller of any of those creatures may pay 2 life to
          prevent that creature from being buried. Effects that prevent or
          redirect damage cannot be used to counter this loss of life. Use
          this ability only when Giant Albatross is put into the graveyard
          from play.

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_G.guide/GIALB}

@endnode
@node GIOYS "Giant Oyster"

@{b}Giant Oyster@{ub}

Color   = Blue
Rarity  = HL(U3)
Type    = Summon Oyster (0/3)
Cost    = 2UU
Artist  = Nicola Leonard

Text(HL): You may choose not to untap Giant Oyster during your untap phase.
          <T>: Target tapped creature does not untap during its controller's
          untap phase as long as Giant Oyster remains tapped. During your
          upkeep, put a -1/-1 counter on that creature. If Giant Oyster
          becomes untapped or leaves play, remove all of these counters
          from the creature.

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_G.guide/GIOYS}

@endnode
